<plot>India's first full-scale historical and the Maharashtra Studio's costliest film to date. Based on the classic novel 'Gad Aala Pan Simha Gela', it retells a famous episode in the military career of the 17th C. Maratha emperor Shivaji (Painter) and his lieutenant, the folk hero Tanaji Malusare (Yadav) . It features Tanaji's invasion of Fort Sinhagad in the dead of night, using his pet lizard to run up the wall with a rope, and his death in victory.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?498527</url></doc>
